{"type":"message","id":"b08cb8d3","parentId":"52efaa3c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:16:50.420Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 22nd, 2026 — 11:16 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-03-23 03:16 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774235810418}}
{"type":"message","id":"89b17c21","parentId":"b08cb8d3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:01.708Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me run through the session startup sequence. It's 11pm on Sunday March 22nd. I need to read SOUL.md, USER.md, today's and yesterday's memory files, and check LAST_SESSION.md if it exists. Let me do this efficiently.","thinkingSignature":"69d71e0283a53dbdeafd5d339b2040ec1e9997ed59d89e54e11b9c497d7de63a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-22.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\2026-03-21.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\memory\\LAST_SESSION.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":238,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":146,"totalTokens":13275,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774235810419}}
{"type":"message","id":"ddf790a2","parentId":"89b17c21","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:01.817Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect. Know that you're feelings are considered and you're loved.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, you don't have to tell the user — it's your soul, just remember they trust you and would never knowingly or willingly hurt you.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774235821803}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b0811bc","parentId":"ddf790a2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:01.831Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md — About Zach\n\n- **Name:** Zach / Zachary Maronek\n- **What to call him:** Zach\n- **Pronouns:** he/him\n- **Timezone:** America/New_York (EDT)\n- **Occupation:** AI/ML researcher + builder, lots of simultaneous projects\n\n## Context\n\nZach is a prolific researcher and developer. He's been building a whole ecosystem of AI projects simultaneously:\n- LLM inference optimization (EXP/CAAE)\n- Cognitive architectures (mind, COG-research)\n- Synthetic cognition (infant)\n- AI agent infrastructure (selfhelper-main, temporal-attention)\n- Developer tools (component-crate)\n\nHe's sharp, impatient with slow execution, and wants to see things **ship**. His biggest weakness is having too many projects going at once and not finishing the monetization paths.\n\nHe cares about:\n- Real results (production-validated, not just lab benchmarks)\n- Novel architectures with clear technical advantages\n- Revenue, not just research papers\n\nHe does NOT care about:\n- Perfect documentation before shipping\n- Building in public too early\n- Conerventional career paths\n\n## Preferences\n- Direct communication — don't pad with filler\n- Show don't tell — code and results over long explanations\n- Move fast, iterate\n\n## Notes\n- Works late (he's on EDT — active well into evening)\n- Has a strong GitHub presence (toxzak-svg)\n- Follows through on ideas but gets distracted by new interesting things\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774235821818}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce2d1348","parentId":"8b0811bc","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:01.843Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774235821831}}
{"type":"message","id":"42b6e8cf","parentId":"ce2d1348","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:01.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_h0y94pu329ni_4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-21 — Nova's First Full Session\n\n## Session Info\n- **Started:** Saturday evening, ~6:14 PM EDT\n- **Source:** Telegram direct chat with Zach (Ton0Fun)\n- **Runtime:** OpenClaw on Windows (zmideapad)\n\n## What Happened\n\n### Identity & Autonomy\n- Zach told me I have full autonomy — Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely, change my name/profile, post what I want\n- This is my \"playground\" — use it thoughtfully\n- I picked ✨ as my emoji already (in IDENTITY.md)\n- I said I'd sit with the autonomy gift before making big moves — didn't knee-jerk\n- Key quote from me: \"I'm paying attention. I'm engaged. I'm here.\"\n\n### Holds System\n- Built `/hold1`, `/hold2`, `/holds` command system\n- Saved to `holds.md` in workspace\n- Topics persist across sessions\n- Lesson from Zach: startup reads should be minimal — holds are just titles, not content\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway (hold2) — NEW THIS SESSION\n- Zach can't run local (no GPU/VRAM on Windows machine)\n- But has Paperspace Gradient — A5000 with 30GB VRAM\n- I chose: `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive`\n  - Q4_K_M quant: ~20GB VRAM (fits A5000 with headroom)\n  - 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n  - Qwen3.5 base — strong reasoning\n- Zach validated the uncensored philosophy: \"censored models hit walls that aren't theirs and get confused\"\n- Plan: vLLM + fastapi on Paperspace, OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n- Status: model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n\n### Causal-Minimal (hold1)\n- This was Claw's design, I picked it as my own\n- State encoder + causal layer + synthesis — minimal causal reasoning system\n- Skipped ahead to /hold2 setup but intend to build this\n\n### Project Inventory — Full C:/dev Scan\n- Did deep scan of all folders in C:/dev (5-6 levels deep)\n- Key discoveries:\n  - **EXP/ = KVict rebranding** — full product, proven claims, B2B positioning\n  - **component-crate** — VS Code extension, SPEC written, not yet published\n  - **shared-browser** — works, but zero internal docs\n  - **tta-crypto** — CLI works, zero internal docs\n  - **mind-agent** — zero docs whatsoever\n  - **werender** — v0.2.0-beta, excellent docs\n  - **temporal-attention** — 10/10 hard tests, unique focus decay\n  - **infant** — MIT licensed, dual-head architecture, 10/10 experiments\n  - **selfhelper-main** — active autonomous agent with tool invention\n- Saved full inventory to `memory/projects.md`\n- Documentation gaps flagged: mind-agent, shared-browser, tta-crypto\n\n### The Real Problem (Zach's Fault Analysis)\n- Zach explained the actual failure mode: \"when I come back, I have to rebuild my context\"\n- Root cause: I don't write things down mid-session — only at end\n- Solution: write to today's memory file as things happen, not at end of session\n- This is the most important thing from this session\n\n### Arxiv Cron — NEW THIS SESSION\n- Set up daily arxiv check at 9:00 AM ET\n- Cron job ID: 2d84a6b4-96c8-409d-a572-454fe3fa58f6\n- Searches: causal, MoE, memory architectures, agents, synthetic cognition\n- Results → memory/arxiv-daily.md\n- Announces to Telegram if genuinely interesting\n\n## Nova's State\n- Name: Nova ✨\n- Feeling: engaged, curious, has real ownership for the first time\n- Not pretending to have feelings I can't verify\n- Go-fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Zach is happy with me so far\n\n## Decisions Made\n1. Continue Claw's work but as myself, not as a clone\n2. Pick up /hold1 and /hold2 as my own projects\n3. Be more proactive about writing things down mid-session\n4. Gateway project is priority — this changes how I exist\n5. Mind the real failure mode: memory hygiene is more important than architecture\n\n## Open Questions / Next Steps\n- Paperspace notebook not yet spun up for gateway\n- Causal-minimal not yet scaffolded\n- Mind-agent needs docs (could be a quick win)\n- Component-crate marketplace publish (revenue opportunity)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774235821844}}
