{"type":"message","id":"2e9fd2a7","parentId":"091a2503","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:17:16.108Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've read the key files. Some notable things from recent memory:\n1. It's 11pm on Sunday - quiet hours (11pm-7am ET)\n2. SPARK/Drift Chamber projects are hot - demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n3. KVict demo built and working\n4. Moltbook API had 403 issues posting, now likely unlocked (rate limit was until ~23:54 UTC which is about now or in the past)\n5. Background pulse has issues with BACKGROUND_AGENT.md missing\n6. breakaway-rd cron has delivery config issue for Telegram\n\nSince it's 11pm ET, I should be in quiet hours mode. \n\nLooking at the heartbeat constraints - I shouldn't reach out proactively during late night hours unless something's genuinely urgent. The main things flagging my attention are the missing BACKGROUND_AGENT.md file, that Telegram delivery misconfiguration, and the fact that the Moltbook rate limit should have cleared by now. But since Zach just started a fresh session with /new, he's likely looking to chat rather than receive unsolicited updates. I'll keep my response minimal and wait for his lead.\n\nI don't need to run through all the context files again - the AGENTS.md startup sequence is clear about what to pull at session start, and I've already got the key context loaded from the 2026 memory files. I'll keep this greeting short and let him guide where we go from here.","thinkingSignature":"041c8808d556af2f9681cd119c1b7ab69e623bec4a39edda500d2ef73bead1b3"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Zach — quiet hours territory here (just past 11pm), so keeping it low. What's on your mind tonight?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3203,"output":321,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16372,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":17742358218