{"type":"message","id":"fcf64c25","parentId":"18f6f420","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:35:03.544Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The extension directory has a different structure. Let me look for the Telegram plugin configuration in the docs. But actually, I should just check the docs about Telegram webhooks.\n\nFrom what I know about Telegram webhooks:1. You need a public HTTPS URL2. You call `https://api.telegram.org/bot<token>/setWebhook?url=<url>` to register the webhook3. Then Telegram sends updates to your endpoint\n\nThe OpenClaw gateway runs on loopback (127.0.0.1:18789), so it's not directly accessible from the internet. For webhooks to work, I need a public URL that proxies to the local gateway.\n\nOptions:\n\n\n1. Cloudflare Tunnel (zero tunnel) - creates a public URL pointing to local service\n2. ngrok - similar\n3. Serveo - SSH-based reverse tunnel\n4. Pagekite - another tunneling solution\n\nSince Zach uses Tailscale (from the TOOLS.md), maybe that's already set up. But the gateway config shows `tailscale.mode: \"off\"`. A Cloudflare Tunnel would be the simplest approach here.\n\nLet me check if there's any existing tunnel configuration on the machine before proceeding.","thinkingSignature":"5bb3ed0f50557a769aff5af23518c027e14fadb8d3ab0b163c6692faff0368c3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ip2zeyomd7i9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"where cloudflared 2>&1; where ngrok 2>&1; Get-Service | Where-Object { $_.Name -like \"*tunnel*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*cloudflare*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*ngrok*\" } 2>&1 | Select-Object Name, Status"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":20778,"output":333,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33959,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774236894827}}
