{"type":"message","id":"c47e6b25","parentId":"fa1fdd93","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:35:14.175Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"cloudflared and ngrok aren't in PATH. Let me think about this differently.\n\nFor webhooks, the issue is that the gateway is on loopback only and there's no public URL. Zach has Tailscale mentioned in TOOLS.md but `tailscale.mode: \"off\"`.\n\nOptions:\n1. Enable Tailscale in OpenClaw gateway config — but this requires Tailscale to be installed and authenticated on the machine\n2. Set up a Cloudflare Tunnel (cloudflared) — but it's not installed\n3. Use ngrok — not installed\n\nWait, actually the most practical approach here might be to just use polling for now and see if there's an easy path to webhooks. But Zach specifically asked for webhooks.\n\n\nLet me reconsider the gateway configuration — it has `bind: \"loopback\"` and `mode: \"local\"`, with a public `remoteUrl` field that could potentially expose the gateway if configured. If I enable Tailscale in the config, that might provide the public URL needed for webhooks, assuming Tailscale is already installed and authenticated on the machine.\n\nThe simpler path though is probably checking if Cloudflare Tunnel is available as a system service, since many machines have it installed but not actively running.","thinkingSignature":"c1f1a0c3eb64e0027f7dd7e1438218857acf9eab66e3020b5c2e4e3a18b18e1b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dq1a4oo62515_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Service | Select-Object Name, Status 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":21212,"output":299,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34359,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774236905162}}
