{"type":"message","id":"9355ab30","parentId":"5ffc231f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:35:42.417Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Tailscale isn't installed. And neither are cloudflared or ngrok.\n\nOK so the situation is:\n- OpenClaw gateway on loopback only\n- No tunnel clients installed\n- No public URL\n\nFor webhooks to work, I fundamentally need a public URL. The options are:\n\n1. **Install and configure a tunnel** — cloudflared is free and easy. I could install it and set up a tunnel to port 18789. This would give a public `*.trycloudflare.com` URL.\n\n2. **Expose gateway directly** — change bind from loopback to all interfaces and set a public remote URL (but Zach's on NAT, no public IP)\n\n\n3. **Use ngrok** — similar to cloudflared but requires an account\n\nInstalling cloudflared and creating a tunnel is the most straightforward path. Let me first check if there's already a public URL I'm missing or if Zach has any existing infrastructure set up.\n\nFor Telegram webhooks specifically, I need a persistent HTTPS URL that Telegram can reach. Zach's home network is behind NAT with no public IP, so a tunnel service is necessary. Let me see if cloudflared is available to install, or if Zach has another tunnel solution already in place.","thinkingSignature":"d1230ffaa79ac3f0105b0261797325312815330867cc84b359d077a7c84d04c0"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Got a problem — Telegram webhooks need a public HTTPS URL, and your gateway is on loopback with no tunnel set up. I'd need to install `cloudflared` (free, no account needed) to create a tunnel to your gateway port 18789, then register that URL with Telegram.\n\nWant me to:\n1. Install cloudflared and spin up the tunnel\n2. Register the webhook with Telegram\n3. Update the gateway config to use the tunnel URL\n\nOr if you'd rather just leave Telegram on polling for now, that's also fine — polling isn't expensive for a low-traffic bot. Let me know how you want to play it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22391,"output":396,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":35635,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774236930856}}
{"type":"message","id":"b473fcfe","parentId":"9355ab30","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:36:17.700Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Sun 2026-03-22 23:36 EDT] 1 is fine thank you hun"}],"timestamp":1774236977698}}
{"type":"message","id":"0facc597","parentId":"b473fcfe","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:36:23.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to proceed with option 1 - install cloudflared and set up the tunnel. Let me do that.","thinkingSignature":"566ab18d4db5bfd508c5f247a17f4e79b3a06b75a5365c70f0cf6e01fc180d71"},{"type":"text","text":"On it.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_oi3nvkts8epx_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"winget install --id Cloudflare.cloudflared -e --silent 2>&1","timeout":120}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":82,"cacheRead":28845,"cacheWrite":5294,"totalTokens":34264,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774236977699}}
