{"type":"message","id":"d7486930","parentId":"0e152bf6","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:38:38.634Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Telegram can reach the gateway through the cloudflare tunnel (HTTP 200). Now I need to restart the gateway so it picks up the new config (public mode instead of loopback).\n\nWait, but there's a problem - cloudflared quick tunnels get a new URL every time they restart. So if Zach reboots his machine or cloudflared restarts, the URL changes and the webhook breaks. That's a known limitation of quick tunnels vs named tunnels.\n\nBut let me first restart the gateway to pick up the config change, then test the full Telegram webhook flow.","thinkingSignature":"ddcb392a48a78c7732dd500af2b9f819928a216c98112051d885d200e27cc4f4"},{"type":"text","text":"Tunnel's healthy and publicly reachable. Now restarting the gateway to apply the public bind mode.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0ju6n7j7ivcq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw gateway restart 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28984,"output":176,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42008,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237110021}}
