{"type":"message","id":"8d7f526e","parentId":"ebe25d91","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:38:52.535Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, I made a mistake. `gateway.mode` only accepts \"local\" or \"remote\", not \"public\". And `gateway.bind` doesn't accept \"all\". Let me fix the config. For webhook to work, the gateway needs to be reachable from the internet, but the issue is that it's behind cloudflare tunnel anyway, so it should still work since the tunnel forwards traffic to localhost:18789 regardless of the bind setting.\n\nLet me revert the gateway config changes. Actually, since we're using cloudflare tunnel, the gateway only needs to listen locally for cloudflared to connect to it. The cloudflare tunnel is what makes it publicly reachable. So I should revert those changes and keep the original loopback config.\n\n\nThe tunnel was working fine when I tested it with curl, so the gateway is clearly accessible through cloudflare even with loopback configured. The webhook was set correctly and Telegram should be able to reach it, so I'll revert my config changes and test the Telegram integration directly.","thinkingSignature":"e31edb5cdec8d680eb4cff37f35382af1990a05f830da6c50e5f4b412d5d7422"},{"type":"text","text":"My bad — `gateway.mode` only accepts `local` or `remote`. Since the cloudflare tunnel handles the public exposure, the local bind is fine. Let me revert that.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_76xyutzh9ljn_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json","old_string":"  \"gateway\": {\n    \"port\": 18789,\n    \"mode\": \"public\",\n    \"bind\": \"all\",","new_string":"  \"gateway\": {\n    \"port\": 18789,\n    \"mode\": \"local\",\n    \"bind\": \"loopback\","}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29412,"output":350,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42610,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"ca