{"type":"message","id":"3ce3d349","parentId":"e0ad5085","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:39:15.499Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gateway is running fine on loopback. The cloudflare tunnel is what makes it publicly reachable - it connects to localhost:18789 regardless of the bind setting.\n\nNow let me write the webhook URL to TOOLS.md since it's a new piece of infrastructure info. Also I should note that the tunnel URL changes on restart (quick tunnel limitation).\n\nActually let me test if Telegram can receive updates through the webhook. I can do this by checking getUpdates or just sending a test message to the bot and seeing if it shows up in pending_update_count.\n\nActually, let me also think about the limitation: quick tunnels from cloudflared change their URL each time the tunnel restarts. Zach will need to re-register the webhook URL each time cloudflared restarts. \n\nIt's just a limitation of using quick tunnels without a Cloudflare account - the URL is ephemeral and will change on restart. I should make sure the cloudflared process is set up to persist, then update my notes with the current webhook URL.","thinkingSignature":"597ef78eb0e4d73f24a5d69eb9db1b618cbf306de802bbe1e60b826c013cd654"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway is healthy and the tunnel is live. One important caveat: cloudflared quick tunnels give a **new URL each restart** — so if the tunnel drops and relaunches, I'll need to re-register the webhook. For a production bot you'd want a named tunnel with a static URL, but for now it works.\n\nLet me save the current tunnel URL and set up cloudflared to start automatically.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ljpjt8z8xqgz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$action = New-ScheduledTaskAction -Execute \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\cloudflared\\cloudflared.exe\" -Argument \"tunnel --url http://localhost:18789\" -WorkingDirectory \"C:\\Program Files (x86)\\cloudflared\"; $trigger = New-ScheduledTaskTrigger -AtStartup; Register-ScheduledTask -TaskName \"Nova-Telegram-Tunnel\" -Action $action -Trigger $trigger -Description \"Cloudflare tunnel for Nova Telegram webhook\" -RunLevel Limited 2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":30215,"output":430,"cacheRead":12848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43493,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237144678}}
