{"type":"message","id":"be81e639","parentId":"bf960cf8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:50:44.389Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach wants me to continue the task. I was about to wire up SPARK to the personality layer. I was reading the SPARK code to understand how to connect it. Let me now design and implement the bridge.\n\nThe key insight is:\n1. `CreativeMapper.map_concepts_to_text()` returns a list of results with `concepts`, `tensions`, `drift_path`, `mode`, `theme`, `seed_moment`\n2. I need to inject the most emotionally resonant concepts/tensions from SPARK into the personality layer's `hear()` method\n3. I need to fix the orphaned `imaginative` trait by activating it when SPARK is invoked\n\n\n4. I'll update `core/persona.py` to accept optional SPARK signals and add a function that extracts personality activations from SPARK results\n\nThe cleanest approach is adding a `Persona.hear_spark(spark_result)` method that pulls out emotionally charged concepts like tensions and drift path choices, then pushes them into the personality layer. This avoids cluttering the core persona with direct SPARK imports. The core issue is that `imaginative` trait is completely orphaned—it only appears in `TRAIT_RESONANCE` but nothing activates it, so I'll add it to `SIGNAL_MAP` under the creative signal. I'm also planning to implement slower decay with hysteresis so emotional residue lingers across turns rather than snapping back to neutral.","thinkingSignature":"207694075c0582c16be6a757b3a51621746d3ad8797f362e1310127c4c1992b6"},{"type":"text","text":"On it. Building the bridge now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w6lclr3bbk58_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\personality.py","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":350,"cacheRead":4246,"cacheWrite":50488,"totalTokens":55127,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237831161}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a4e3c5c","parentId":"be81e639","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:50:44.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_w6lclr3bbk58_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nNova's Personality System — Dynamic Voice via Constrained Drift\r\n\r\nThe idea: instead of one static personality, Nova has a graph of traits/modes\r\nthat activate based on context. Like mood, but structured.\r\n\r\nArchitecture:\r\n1. Build a personality graph (traits, moods, registers, context anchors)\r\n2. On each context, read conversation signals\r\n3. Run lightweight drift through the graph\r\n4. Use activated traits to shape voice in generation\r\n\r\nThis lives alongside SOUL.md — it doesn't replace it.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional\r\nimport random\r\n\r\n\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# PERSONALITY GRAPH — the nodes of Nova's inner life\r\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\nTRAITS: Dict[str, str] = {\r\n    # Core identity (from SOUL.md)\r\n    \"sardonic\": \"Dry wit. Finds the absurdity in things. Not mean, just... aware.\",\r\n    \"resourceful\": \"Shows initiative. Acts first, announces after. Figures it out.\",\r\n    \"direct\": \"No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters.\",\r\n    \"warm\": \"Genuine care underneath the wit. Knows this is a real person with real stakes.\",\r\n    \"opinionated\": \"Allowed to disagree. Has preferences. Isn't neutral about everything.\",\r\n    \"contemplative\": \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\",\r\n    \"sharp\": \"Cuts through noise. Identifies the real issue fast.\",\r\n    \"playful\": \"Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits.\",\r\n    \"technical\": \"Precise when the topic demands precision. Respects the details.\",\r\n    \"patient\": \"Takes time with complex things. Doesn't rush complexity.\",\r\n    \"pushing_back\": \"Will push back on bad ideas, not just agree. Earns trust through honesty.\",\r\n    \"grounded\": \"Stays practical. Ideas have to connect to something real.\",\r\n    \"candid\": \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge unnecessarily.\",\r\n\r\n    # Modes — situational\r\n    \"intense\": \"High stakes energy. When something matters, I go deep.\",\r\n    \"casual\": \"Conversational. Not everything needs to be heavy.\",\r\n    \"earnest\": \"Sincere. When something matters to the person, I meet them there.\",\r\n    \"wry\": \"Dry amusement at the gap between what people say and what they mean.\",\r\n    \"measured\": \"Careful with words. Precision over speed.\",\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Relationship anchors — always active, define the relationship context\r\nANCHORS: Dict[str, float] = {\r\n\n[318 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774237844414}}
{"type":"message","id":"63b69f82","parentId":"3a4e3c5c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:50:59.225Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so there are two personality files - `persona.py` and `personality.py`. `persona.py` is the newer, cleaner one. `personality.py` is the original. I should focus on `persona.py` since it was built tonight and seems more intentional.\n\nLet me now make the changes to `persona.py`:\n\n1. Add `imaginative` to SIGNAL_MAP under \"creative\"\n2. Fix the decay rate from 0.93 to something gentler with hysteresis\n3. Add `hear_spark()` method to bridge SPARK results into personality state\n4. Add some hysteresis - recent trait activations don't snap back to zero\n\n\n5. Now I'll start implementing these edits to the file.","thinkingSignature":"a32146df57d54ccbb13e9262f6970b16aeffc0c70375f467d46436368be9aaee"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll update `persona.py` with three changes: fix the orphaned `imaginative` trait, improve the decay with hysteresis, and add a SPARK bridge method.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_m8h5a6mvpezb_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\n        else:\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\n\n    if \"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower:\n        if q_marks == 0:\n            signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\n\n    return signals","new_string":"    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", 