{"type":"message","id":"21dc9ff6","parentId":"536a3e0b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:51:54.726Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to also fix the orphaned `imaginative` trait. It's defined in `TRAITS` but nothing activates it directly. I've now wired it up through `MODE_SIGNALS` in `hear_spark`, but it still needs to be in `TRAITS`. Let me check if `imaginative` is already in `TRAITS`.\n\nLooking at the original `TRAITS` in `persona.py`, I see it has 18 traits but doesn't include `imaginative`. The `TRAIT_RESONANCE` dict has `imaginative` as a key, and `SIGNAL_MAP` doesn't activate it. My fix added it to `MODE_SIGNALS` for `hear_spark`, but it won't be activated through the normal `hear()` path.\n\n\nThe simplest fix is to add `imaginative` directly to the `SIGNAL_MAP` under the creative signal so it gets activated through the normal flow too.","thinkingSignature":"683bfff4fdbf7c5ea386651c98d04b4113d8e0fe6b92af94a46be0cc0f0cd364"},{"type":"text","text":"One more fix — `imaginative` is in `TRAIT_RESONANCE` but nothing in `SIGNAL_MAP` activates it. Let me add it to the `creative` signal.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qxyu659o0r72_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],","new_string":"    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],\n    \"creative\":     [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"],"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46130,"output":363,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59550,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237905823}}
