{"type":"message","id":"183c9f37","parentId":"47539e32","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:52:01.350Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, that's a duplicate key which would just override itself in Python dict literals. Let me fix this properly - I need to add \"imaginative\" to the existing \"creative\" entry, not create a duplicate.Actually, wait - looking at the edit, the SIGNAL_MAP already has \"creative\" as a key with [\"playful\", \"contemplative\", \"earnest\", \"imaginative\"]. My edit accidentally duplicated it. Let me fix this - I'll just remove the duplicate.\n\nActually let me re-read the SIGNAL_MAP in the current file to see what it looks like now.","thinkingSignature":"90b0330bc4f08e4acdd2fb5778e50623853e1b4a1fc679224f486dce038a1b0f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sr1y6qwbpk6o_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","offset":100,"limit":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46530,"output":182,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59769,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237914744}}
{"type":"message","id":"a36915b3","parentId":"183c9f37","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:52:01.366Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sr1y6qwbpk6o_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    signals[\"light\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"haha\", \"lol\", \"funny\", \"😄\", \"joke\", \"lighter\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n    signals[\"vulnerable\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"honestly\", \"truthfully\", \"scared\", \"not sure\", \"vulnerable\", \"worried\"\n    ]) else 0.0\n\n    # Interaction type\n    q_marks = text.count(\"?\")\n    if q_marks > 0:\n        if any(w in lower for w in [\"what do you think\", \"how would you\", \"opinion\", \"thoughts\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_opinion\"] = 0.9\n        elif any(w in lower for w in [\"how do i\", \"can you\", \"what is\", \"help\"]):\n            signals[\"asks_help\"] = 0.8\n        else:\n            signals[\"asks_something\"] = 0.6\n\n    if \"i've been\" in lower or \"i just\" in lower or \"so today\" in lower:\n        if q_marks == 0:\n            signals[\"sharing\"] = 0.8\n\n    return signals\n\n\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n# SPARK BRIDGE — inject SPARK results into personality\n# -------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n# Map emotional tension keywords to personality signals\nTENSION_TO_SIGNAL = {\n\n[305 more lines in file. Use offset=130 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774237921359}}
