{"type":"message","id":"a7f5b1c1","parentId":"44926a70","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:52:40.598Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ANCHORS dict has string values in `persona.py`, but the `guide()` method is checking `if val > 0.7` treating them as floats. The original `personality.py` had ANCHORS as floats. The `persona.py` ANCHORS are descriptions (strings), not activation values. So `guide()` is comparing strings to floats, which causes the error.\n\nI need to fix the `guide()` method to not treat anchor values as floats. Since anchors are always active (they don't decay), I should just show all the anchors that are defined, not filter by a float threshold. Or I should add a separate ANCHORS_META dict that defines which anchors are \"on\" by default.","thinkingSignature":"370d78d9f65925b6482f8096c1448b2ff05c0fb812dd7b761944f1ef9f211e9e"},{"type":"text","text":"\nThe `ANCHORS` in `persona.py` are descriptions (strings), not activation values. The `guide()` method was written expecting float activations. Let me fix the `guide()` method to handle string-anchors properly.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_r9icrag1uz0c_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"        anchor_lines = [\n            f\"  • {name}: yes\"\n            for name, val in self.anchors.items()\n            if val > 0.7\n        ]","new_string":"        anchor_lines = [\n            f\"  • {name}\"\n            for name in self.anchors\n        ]"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":48871,"output":322,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62250,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774237952534}}
