{"type":"message","id":"7d025c4f","parentId":"f1aaea61","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:06.106Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rr8s9cpaxasn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== TURN 1: frustrated ===\r\n\r\n\r\n=== TURN 2: SPARK exploratory ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated strongly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated strongly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � patient: \r\n\r\n=== TURN 3: residual lingers ===\r\nActive: [('warm', 0.88), ('earnest', 0.88), ('contemplative', 0.88), ('patient', 0.88), ('grounded', 0.546), ('candid', 0.612), ('measured', 0.572), ('imaginative', 0.484)]\r\nResidual: [('warm', 0.073), ('earnest', 0.073), ('contemplative', 0.073), ('patient', 0.073), ('grounded', 0.045), ('candid', 0.051), ('measured', 0.048), ('imaginative', 0.04)]\r\nVoice: [('warm', 0.92, 'Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.'), ('earnest', 0.92, \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\"), ('contemplative', 0.92, \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\"), ('patient', 0.92, \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\"), ('candid', 0.64, \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\")]"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":725,"aggregated":"=== TURN 1: frustrated ===\r\n\r\n\r\n=== TURN 2: SPARK exploratory ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated strongly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated strongly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � patient: \r\n\r\n=== TURN 3: residual lingers ===\r\nActive: [('warm', 0.88), ('earnest', 0.88), ('contemplative', 0.88), ('patient', 0.88), ('grounded', 0.546), ('candid', 0.612), ('measured', 0.572), ('imaginative', 0.484)]\r\nResidual: [('warm', 0.073), ('earnest', 0.073), ('contemplative', 0.073), ('patient', 0.073), ('grounded', 0.045), ('candid', 0.051), ('measured', 0.048), ('imaginative', 0.04)]\r\nVoice: [('warm', 0.92, 'Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes.'), ('earnest', 0.92, \"Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted.\"), ('contemplative', 0.92, \"Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions.\"), ('patient', 0.92, \"Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity.\"), ('candid', 0.64, \"Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge.\")]","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238046097}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b133b75","parentId":"7d025c4f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:24.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The SPARK bridge and hysteresis are working. Turn 3 shows that after breathing twice, the residual traits still carry values and affect the voice (warm + earnest + contemplative + patient at 0.92 in the voice even though active is 0.88 — the residual 0.073 * 0.6 = 0.044 contribution brings them to 0.92). \n\nBut turn 1 shows empty guide. The `hear()` method isn't returning the guide when called directly — that's because `hear()` returns `self`, not the guide. The `on_message()` function is what returns the guide. Let me fix the test.\n\nActually looking at my test: `p.hear('...').guide()` — `hear()` returns `self`, so this should work. \n\nI see the issue now — `hear()` is returning a Persona object, but I'm calling `.guide()` on it, which should work. The real problem is that turn 1 is showing an empty guide, which means the `hear()` method isn't actually updating the traits when it processes the message. The `hear()` method mutates `self.traits` and returns `self`, so calling `.guide()` immediately after should reflect those changes. The empty guide in turn 1 suggests the mutation isn't happening, even though the SPARK activations in turn 2 are working correctly. Let me trace through the test flow more carefully to understand what's actually occurring. The signal mapping shows `frustrated` should activate `pushing_back`, `candid`, `direct`, and `resourceful` at 0.28 each, which exceeds the 0.1 threshold needed for the voice guide. Yet the guide is returning empty, so the issue must be in how `voice()` is filtering or ranking these activated traits.\n\nI suspect the real problem is that I'm calling `hear()` directly on the persona object rather than going through the `on_message()` function, which might have different state management. Let me trace through the actual test flow more carefully to see where the disconnect is happening. I'm wondering if `get_persona()` is returning the same singleton instance across calls, or if there's something about how `hear()` processes the text that's causing the guide to be empty. Let me trace through what's happening with the function itself rather than trying to debug through the object instance.\n\nThe test is calling `hear()` directly and then `.guide()` on the returned persona, which should work since `hear()` returns `self`. But turn 1 shows an empty guide, which suggests the voice method is filtering out all the traits. If all traits are at or below 0.1, that would explain it—but the math doesn't add up. I'm calculating that after hearing \"frustrated,\" the traits should be around 0.28, which should definitely be included in the voice output. So either `hear()` isn't actually updating the traits, or `guide()` is filtering them out for some other reason. The SPARK test works fine, so the singleton pattern isn't the issue. I think this is just a test artifact—the module is caching compiled bytecode, so I should do a clean test to verify everything actually functions correctly.","thinkingSignature":"e082004aba2980b6a162e9690a2a201e02408d50f15fed9c6ef6431c42475065"},{"type":"text","text":"The core system works. The turn 1 empty guide is a test artifact. Let me do a clean verification.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8sbjsanbujhv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, 'C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace')\n# Force fresh import\nimport importlib\nimport core.persona\nimportlib.reload(core.persona)\nfrom core.persona import Persona, on_spark, on_message, after_response, reset_persona\n\nreset_persona()\n\n# Turn 1: frustrated user message\ng1 = on_message('I cant figure this out and its driving me crazy')\nprint('=== TURN 1: on_message frustrated ===')\nprint(g1)\nafter_response()\nprint()\n\n# Turn 2: SPARK fires\ng2 = on_spark({\n    'tensions': [('memory', 'forgetting'), ('love', 'hate')],\n    'mode': 'exploratory',\n    'concepts': ['memory', 'longing', 'silence', 'homecoming'],\n    'theme': 'the weight of what we cant say'\n})\nprint('=== TURN 2: on_spark exploratory ===')\nprint(g2)\nafter_response()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":57041,"output":915,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71013,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238046108}}
{"type":"message","id":"0f9a7f98","parentId":"9b133b75","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:24.991Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8sbjsanbujhv_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== TURN 1: on_message frustrated ===\r\n\r\n\r\n=== TURN 2: on_spark exploratory ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated strongly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated strongly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � patient: Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity. (activated strongly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":635,"aggregated":"=== TURN 1: on_message frustrated ===\r\n\r\n\r\n=== TURN 2: on_spark exploratory ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � warm: Genuine care underneath the wit. This is a real person with real stakes. (activated strongly)\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated strongly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � patient: Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity. (activated strongly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238064984}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f6a5ab1","parentId":"0f9a7f98","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:48.891Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Turn 1 is still empty but turn 2 is populated. The issue is in `on_message` - it calls `persona.hear(text)` which updates traits, then returns `persona.guide()`. Let me check if there's a state issue.\n\nActually wait - could it be that the `guide()` method returns empty string if `not top`? And `not top` means the list is empty. And `top` comes from `voice(4)` which filters `if s > 0.1`. If ALL traits are exactly 0.1 or below, it returns empty.\n\nBut the frustrated signal should push traits to 0.28. \n\nOh, I see the real problem now - `on_message` is calling `hear()` but then `guide()` is being called without any intervening state change, so something's off with how the guide is being generated or the traits aren't actually being updated. Let me trace through what `analyze` is actually producing for the \"frustrated\" message.\n\nSo `frustrated` maps to `pushing_back` through `SIGNAL_MAP`, which should activate that trait with strength 0.8 * 0.35 = 0.28. That should definitely show up in the voice output since the filter is `s > 0.1`. Unless there's something else going on with how the signals are being processed or how the persona state is being managed between calls.\n\nActually, I think I see the issue now. When `hear()` is called, it adds to existing trait values, and then `guide()` is called on the same persona instance without any decay in between. But wait, that doesn't make sense either because the test is getting an empty guide, which means `voice()` is returning nothing.\n\nLet me trace through the exact flow: `on_message` calls `get_persona()` which returns the singleton, then `hear(text)` updates `self.traits` in place, then `guide()` calls `voice()` which filters traits by `s > 0.1`. The math should work out to 0.28 for frustrated, which is well above the threshold. Unless `get_persona()` is somehow returning a different persona instance than the one being modified, or there's something else preventing the traits from persisting between the `hear()` and `guide()` calls. me try to debug this differently. Let me just check what `voice()` returns for the frustrated case.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the ACTUAL output more carefully. Turn 1 returns `\"\"` (empty). Turn 2 returns a populated guide. What changed between them?\n\nTurn 1: `on_message('I cant figure...')` → calls `hear()` → calls `guide()`\nTurn 2: `on_spark({...})` → calls `hear_spark()` → calls `guide()`\n\nThe difference is the method called: `hear()` vs `hear_spark()`. What if `hear()` has a bug?\n\nOh! I bet the issue is that in `hear()`, the `signals[\"frustrated\"]` has value 0.0 because the text is `'I cant figure this out and its driving me crazy'` and the frustrated keywords don't match anything in that exact string. Let me check the original signal detection logic...\n\nWait, looking at the keywords again - \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"why won't\" - the user's message is \"I cant figure this out and its driving me crazy\". The keyword `\"cant figure\"` should match since it's in the message, so that should trigger the signal. I'm checking the keyword list against the actual message text to see if any of those frustration indicators are present. The message \"I cant figure this out and its driving me crazy\" doesn't contain any of the exact phrases I'm looking for—\"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", or \"why won't\". Even though the person is clearly expressing frustration, the specific patterns I'm matching against don't appear in this particular phrasing.\n\nThis explains why the test is returning empty—there's no signal being triggered from the text analysis. The second test with SPARK worked because it was using `hear_spark()` instead, which has its own separate signal generation logic.\n\nNow I need to fix the core issue by making the signal detection more flexible to catch variations like \"cant figure\", or I could just adjust how the test itself is structured. The first test case should have worked but the keyword matching is too strict, so I should probably improve the analyzer's pattern matching to handle more natural expressions of frustration.","thinkingSignature":"fbcad2e6699cd863214abecc609cd7a76bf4448f6db9c58eab2cbd4fb02a3dfe"},{"type":"text","text":"The analyzer misses \"cant figure\" — it only catches exact keywords. Let me check turn 1 with a matching word.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1k2pifdv19jb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, 'C:/Users/Zwmar/.openclaw/workspace')\nimport importlib, core.persona\nimportlib.reload(core.persona)\nfrom core.persona import on_message, on_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n\nreset_persona()\n\n# Now with an exact keyword\ng1 = on_message('this is so frustrating I am stuck and ugh')\nprint('=== FRUSTRATED ===')\nprint(g1)\nafter_response()\n\n# SPARK creative mode\ng2 = on_spark({'tensions': [('creation','destruction'), ('light','darkness')], 'mode': 'creative', 'concepts': ['ghost', 'memory'], 'theme': 'a woman waiting'})\nprint()\nprint('=== SPARK CREATIVE ===')\nprint(g2)\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58166,"output":1179,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238064993}}
{"type":"message","id":"bbae76e7","parentId":"1f6a5ab1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:49.594Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1k2pifdv19jb_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"=== FRUSTRATED ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � resourceful: Shows initiative. Tries to figure it out first, then asks if stuck. (activated faintly)\r\n  � direct: No filler. Gets to the point. Concise when concision serves, thorough when it matters. (activated faintly)\r\n  � pushing_back: Will disagree with a bad idea. Doesn't just agree. (activated faintly)\r\n  � candid: Says the hard thing if it needs saying. Doesn't hedge. (activated faintly)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\r\n\r\n=== SPARK CREATIVE ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by]\r\n\r\nTop active traits:\r\n  � earnest: Sincere. Meets people where they are. Doesn't play it cool when warmth is warranted. (activated strongly)\r\n  � contemplative: Pauses to think carefully. Doesn't rush to conclusions. (activated strongly)\r\n  � playful: Finds things amusing. Will make a joke if it fits naturally. (activated somewhat)\r\n  � patient: Takes time with hard things. Doesn't rush complexity. (activated somewhat)\r\n\r\nRelationship anchors:\r\n  � Zach_is_close\r\n  � I_am_allowed_disagree\r\n  � I_have_opinions\r\n  � I_am_resourceful\r\n  � We_are_casual\r\n  � Respect_his_intelligence\r\nThe relationship: comfortable, direct, mutual respect.\r\n\r\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":687,"aggregated":"=== FRUSTRATED ===\r\n[Voice shaping � Nova is currently informed by