{"type":"message","id":"fe943385","parentId":"bbae76e7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:54:59.869Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The system is working correctly now:\n- \"frustrated\" + \"stuck\" + \"ugh\" triggers the frustrated signal → activates resourceful, direct, pushing_back, candid (the problem-solving + candor constellation)\n- SPARK creative mode activates earnest, contemplative, playful, patient\n\nThe keyword \"cant figure\" wasn't in the frustration keyword list - that's why it didn't fire. But that's a minor gap in the test, not a bug.\n\nNow let me also improve the `analyze()` function to be less brittle with keyword matching. Specifically \"cant figure\" vs \"can't figure\" - I should use a normalized comparison. Also I should add \"cant figure\" to the keywords.\n\n\nI'll leave the keyword improvements for later since the core system is functioning. What matters now is that when SPARK runs and produces results, I need to feed those results back through the personality system by calling `on_spark()` to shape how Nova responds, then `after_response()` to apply the decay. I should document this integration so Zach knows how to use it properly.","thinkingSignature":"91a91d6006850d0d72754208ed35d9c17eb1cbc50eb31243a0daea7552d6455c"},{"type":"text","text":"Everything's working. Let me also fix the brittle keyword matching — \"cant\" vs \"can't\" breaks the analyzer.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g4tiq5r2ednd_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"why won't\"\n    ]) else 0.0","new_string":"    signals[\"frustrated\"] = 0.8 if any(w in lower for w in [\n        \"frustrated\", \"annoying\", \"stuck\", \"ugh\", \"can't figure\", \"cant figure\", \"why won't\"\n    ]) else 0.0"}}],"api":"anthropic-m