{"type":"message","id":"42334b15","parentId":"cd50f4c1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:55:07.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also make sure the TOOLS.md is updated with the new personality layer info and how to use SPARK integration. Actually, I should also think about what happens next - how does Nova actually USE this in her responses? The current flow is:\n\n1. User sends message → `on_message()` → get voice guide → Nova writes response\n2. SPARK runs → `on_spark()` → get voice guide → Nova writes response\n3. Response sent → `after_response()` → decay\n\nBut Nova isn't actually calling these from her actual response generation. These are just utility functions that update state. The actual \"integration\" would require Nova to call these at the right time in her actual response generation.\n\n\nI should write up a summary of what I've built and how it works, then commit the changes.","thinkingSignature":"6ca2a87fb10d011aebf8dfe3c9069163fce2ada128c89e9ad7c61548268eed11"},{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now let me commit the work and summarize what was built.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g3rqdf64zevj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && git add core/persona.py && git diff --cached --stat"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60171,"output":230,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73458,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238099895}}
