{"type":"message","id":"d0db7e87","parentId":"b92599cb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:55:18.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file is new to git (wasn't tracked before). Let me commit it.","thinkingSignature":"82336e43fa71441f4f5e92941959ad45289f071bc586b13fd127b99e3c23efc9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_agzlxf6q9qfi_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && git commit -m \"persona.py: SPARK bridge, hysteresis decay, imaginative fix\n\n- Add hear_spark() bridge: inject SPARK tensions/mode/concepts into trait state\n- Fix decay with hysteresis: active bleeds into residual, residual decays at 0.975\n- Fix orphaned imaginative trait: added to SIGNAL_MAP[creative]\n- TENSION_TO_SIGNAL map: 20 creative tension pairs → personality signals\n- MODE_SIGNALS: creative/divergent/exploratory each push different trait clusters\n- Fix ANCHORS guide rendering (was comparing strings to float)\n- Add cant/cannot pattern to frustrated signal detection\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60573,"output":186,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238112041}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1612bce","parentId":"d0db7e87","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:55:19.513Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_agzlxf6q9qfi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master 2778a67] persona.py: SPARK bridge, hysteresis decay, imaginative fix\n 1 file changed, 433 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 core/persona.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":746,"aggregated":"[master 2778a67] persona.py: SPARK bridge, hysteresis decay, imaginative fix\n 1 file changed, 433 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 core/persona.py","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238119506}}
{"type":"message","id":"43a5f03c","parentId":"d1612bce","timestamp":"2026-03-23T03:55:27.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now let me give Zach a clean summary of what was built and how it works.","thinkingSignature":"e46281cefb4c56d3327bc5b7aaf0ca30854d53ae9a62f4a37c743d78a538543a"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Done. Here's what got built into `core/persona.py`:\n\n**The SPARK bridge** — `hear_spark(result)` takes SPARK output and maps it into personality state:\n- Mode signals: `exploratory` → contemplative + measured; `creative` → earnest + imaginative; `divergent` → imaginative + intense\n- Tension signals: 20 creative tension pairs (memory/forgetting, love/hate, etc.) each push specific trait clusters\n- High-resonance concepts: \"longing\", \"grief\", \"silence\", \"ghost\" etc. get extra earnest + contemplative weight\n\n**Hysteresis decay** — traits don't snap back to zero after a response. Active bleeds into residual (slow-decay pool), residual feeds back into voice for several turns. Emotional registers fade rather than cut.\n\n**Fixed** — `imaginative` was orphaned (in resonance map, nothing activated it). Now wired through the `creative` signal and SPARK mode signals.\n\n**How it actually works end-to-end:** when SPARK fires and produces a result dict, you call `on_spark(result)` and use the returned voice guide to shape the response. Then `after_response()` handles the decay. The module is stateful — the hysteresis carries context across turns.\n\nThe `on_message()` path works the same way for normal conversation. Both update the same shared `Persona` singleton, so SPARK and conversation state blend naturally."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60814,"output":324,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":74195,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774238119515}}
