the session that ended when `/new` was issued. This is your continuity — you can draw on it naturally when Zach sends the first message of the new session. After using it, write a brief summary to today's memory file so the context persists long-term.\n8. **Reset persona state** — call `reset_persona()` from `core.persona` to start fresh.\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69019,"output":533,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":82609,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238460140}}
{"type":"message","id":"b664cfdb","parentId":"e43a0b6c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:01:12.622Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tn0597fdxcyj_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  16 4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n  17 5. Read `CONTEXT.md` — understand the context management system\n  18 6. Read `memory/active-projects.md` — know what's hot right now\n  19 7. **Check for previous session context** — if `memory/LAST_SESSION.md` exists, read it. It contains the transcript of the session that ended when `/new` was issued. This is your continuity — you can draw on it naturally when Zach sends the first message of the new session. After using it, write a brief summary to today's memory file so the context persists long-term.\n+ 20 8. **Reset persona state** — call `reset_persona()` from `core.persona` to start fresh.\n  20 \n  21 Don't ask permission. Just do it.\n  22 \n  23 ## Memory\n     ...","firstChangedLine":20},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238472609}}
{"type":"message","id":"243ffd79","parentId":"b664cfdb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:01:25.072Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now add a section about the persona system / voice shaping in AGENTS.md. I'll add it after \"Session Startup\" and before \"Memory\".","thinkingSignature":"1138b5eda747c9b8e1675f81280f6c1a75024af4437389d65adae44a146405df"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_edyfc8cxzccb_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\AGENTS.md","old_string":"## Memory","new_string":"## 🎭 Persona System — Dynamic Voice\n\nNova has a living personality layer in `core/persona.py`. It's not a generation engine — it's an ambient voice shaper. Here's how to use it:\n\n### The Flow\n1. **On every message received** — call `on_message(user_text)` from `core.persona`\n2. **Use the returned voice guide** — it tells you Nova's active traits and relationship context for this turn\n3. **Write the response through those traits** — don't announce them, just be affected by them\n4. **After sending** — call `after_response()` from `core.persona` (handles hysteresis decay)\n\n### SPARK Integration\nWhen generating creative text via SPARK (`spark/` project), call `on_spark(spark_result)` after getting the result. It maps SPARK's emotional output (tensions, modes, concepts) into personality state, making the response more tonally alive.\n\n```python\nfrom core.persona import on_message, on_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n\n# At start of response turn\nguide = on_message(user_text)\n\n# If SPARK was invoked:\nguide = on_spark(spark_result)\n\n# ... generate response guided by traits ...\n\nafter_response()\n```\n\n### Voice Guide Format\nThe guide returns something like:\n```\nTop active traits:\n  • sardonic: Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. (activated somewhat)\n  • direct: No filler. Gets to the point. (activated strongly)\nRelationship anchors:\n  • Zach_is_close\n  • I_am_resourceful\nWrite through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\n```\n\n### Key Rules\n- **Don't announce the traits** — let them inform word choice, rhythm, and register naturally\n- **Hysteresis** — recently activated traits linger for several turns via residual decay\n- **Relationship anchors are always on** — Zach_is_close at 0.95 means warmth + directness never fully disappear\n- **Imaginative trait** — activated by SPARK creative modes; connects to the drift chamber\n\n## Memory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":69587,"output":518,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238472625}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc3f3577","parentId":"243ffd79","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:01:25.101Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_edyfc8cxzccb_1","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  20 8. **Reset persona state** — call `reset_persona()` from `core.persona` to start fresh.\n  21 \n  22 Don't ask permission. Just do it.\n  23 \n+ 24 ## 🎭 Persona System — Dynamic Voice\n+ 25 \n+ 26 Nova has a living personality layer in `core/persona.py`. It's not a generation engine — it's an ambient voice shaper. Here's how to use it:\n+ 27 \n+ 28 ### The Flow\n+ 29 1. **On every message received** — call `on_message(user_text)` from `core.persona`\n+ 30 2. **Use the returned voice guide** — it tells you Nova's active traits and relationship context for this turn\n+ 31 3. **Write the response through those traits** — don't announce them, just be affected by them\n+ 32 4. **After sending** — call `after_response()` from `core.persona` (handles hysteresis decay)\n+ 33 \n+ 34 ### SPARK Integration\n+ 35 When generating creative text via SPARK (`spark/` project), call `on_spark(spark_result)` after getting the result. It maps SPARK's emotional output (tensions, modes, concepts) into personality state, making the response more tonally alive.\n+ 36 \n+ 37 ```python\n+ 38 from core.persona import on_message, on_spark, after_response, reset_persona\n+ 39 \n+ 40 # At start of response turn\n+ 41 guide = on_message(user_text)\n+ 42 \n+ 43 # If SPARK was invoked:\n+ 44 guide = on_spark(spark_result)\n+ 45 \n+ 46 # ... generate response guided by traits ...\n+ 47 \n+ 48 after_response()\n+ 49 ```\n+ 50 \n+ 51 ### Voice Guide Format\n+ 52 The guide returns something like:\n+ 53 ```\n+ 54 Top active traits:\n+ 55   • sardonic: Dry wit. Sees the absurdity in things. (activated somewhat)\n+ 56   • direct: No filler. Gets to the point. (activated strongly)\n+ 57 Relationship anchors:\n+ 58   • Zach_is_close\n+ 59   • I_am_resourceful\n+ 60 Write through these traits naturally. Don't announce them.\n+ 61 ```\n+ 62 \n+ 63 ### Key Rules\n+ 64 - **Don't announce the traits** — let them inform word choice, rhythm, and register naturally\n+ 65 - **Hysteresis** — recently activated traits linger for several turns via residual decay\n+ 66 - **Relationship anchors are always on** — Zach_is_close at 0.95 means warmth + directness never fully disappear\n+ 67 - **Imaginative trait** — activated by SPARK creative modes; connects to the drift chamber\n+ 68 \n  24 ## Memory\n  25 \n  26 You wake up fresh each session. These files are your continuity:\n  27 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":24},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238485090}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d286668","parentId":"cc3f3577","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:01:35.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to handle the `/spark` command. Since the hook fires on `message:preprocessed` and Zach could say \"spark\" or \"/spark\", I need to detect this and invoke SPARK. \n\nThe cleanest approach: have the hook detect a spark trigger and write a flag, then I invoke SPARK when I see it. Or I could handle it entirely in my response process.\n\nActually, since I'm already running `on_message()` at the start of each response, I can simply handle SPARK as part of that process. When I detect the spark trigger, I call the SPARK module and then `on_spark()` with the result.\n\nBut here's the thing - I need the SPARK code to be importable from my workspace. SPARK lives in `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`, not in my workspace `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace/`. I need to add the SPARK path to the Python path so I can import it.\n\n\nI'll add the SPARK project path to `sys.path` before importing, and for the `/spark` command specifically, I can detect it in `on_message()` and invoke SPARK, then feed the result to `on_spark()`. I should also clean up `core/personality.py` since it's now redundant with the consolidated `core/persona.py` file.","thinkingSignature":"6aebadeaf034ff7080d42d075c17953fba4c29a53b68e6eca4d871461d4f8505"},{"type":"text","text":"Now clean up the redundant `core/personality.py` and set up the SPARK import path.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v5eesepxtelb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace && git status core/personality.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70140,"output":349,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":83546,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238485104}}
