{"type":"message","id":"1dc05542","parentId":"69d6fc7f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:01:54.839Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me update the persona module to add the SPARK path so SPARK can be imported. I'll add a small import helper at the top of the persona module.Actually, the SPARK import is in the session-level API functions, not in the module level. I can add the path dynamically in the function. Let me add an `on_spark()` variant that also runs SPARK if needed, or just leave the SPARK invocation as a separate step.\n\nLet me think about what I actually want to work:\n\n1. The persona hook fires on `message:preprocessed`, writes `persona-inbound.md`\n\n\n2. At the start of each response turn, I call `on_message()` from `core.persona` with the message content to get the voice guide\n3. If the message is spark-related, I invoke SPARK and then call `on_spark()` with the result\n4. I write my response shaped by the voice guide, then call `after_response()`\n\nFor the `/spark` command specifically, I need to handle the SPARK invocation. I'll update the session-level `on_spark()` function to import SPARK dynamically when called, and add a `spark_result.json` to `memory/` for the hook to detect.\n\nActually, I realize the hook already captures the full `bodyForAgent` content, so I can check for spark-related triggers there. Let me simplify: I'll add a `run_spark()` function to the persona module that handles the SPARK invocation, and have it write results to `memory/spark-result.json` which the hook can detect. For now, let me focus on the core flow and handle SPARK detection in the response process by importing it dynamically.","thinkingSignature":"6b4182c957df9f2997fee1a11de1673156bd5fa408c3ca8bdf7f894ddac24c29"},{"type":"text","text":"Now add SPARK import capability to the persona module — the spark project lives in a different path.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fk9qv7g1ywxi_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"\"\"\"\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer","new_string":"\"\"\"\npersona.py — Nova's living personality layer\n\nSPARK lives in C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/ — added to path dynamically.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys as _sys\nimport os as _os\n\n# Add SPARK project to path for on_spark() dynamic import\n_SPARK_PATH = r\"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark\"\nif _SPARK_PATH not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PATH)\nif _SPARK_PATH not in _sys.path:\n    _sys.path.insert(0, _SPARK_PATH.replace(\"\\\\\", \"/\"))  # try forward slash too"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70727,"output":583,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84367,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238501102}}
