{"type":"message","id":"66b309d9","parentId":"be4aa4c8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:02:03.398Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to handle the `/spark` command. When the user says \"spark\" or \"/spark\", I need to actually run SPARK. Let me update `on_spark()` to optionally invoke SPARK if the user is asking for it.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is:\n1. `on_spark()` takes an optional `invoke=True` parameter that actually runs SPARK\n2. When `invoke=True`, it calls the SPARK demo with appropriate parameters\n3. The result dict is then used to update personality state\n\nOr, I could have a separate function `run_spark()` that invokes SPARK and returns the result.\n\nLet me create a `run_spark()` function that:\n\n\n- Runs the SPARK drift chamber\n- Returns the result in the format `on_spark()` expects\n- Calls `on_spark()` internally with that result\n\nThis way I can do a single call like `guide = run_spark(theme=\"loss and memory\", mode=\"exploratory\")` and it handles everything. Now let me write this function.","thinkingSignature":"af8b3e5acfc590165496594c613e2f290c9e84676c1a83fb7472b238beec0f45"},{"type":"text","text":"\nNow add a `run_spark()` helper to the persona module — the one-call SPARK invocation.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iealu9sewgdb_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","offset":420,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71347,"output":302,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84706,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238514860}}
{"type":"message","id":"f1145555","parentId":"66b309d9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:02:03.414Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_iealu9sewgdb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.hear(text)\n    return persona.guide()\n\n\ndef after_response():\n    \"\"\"Call after sending a response. Mild decay.\"\"\"\n    persona = get_persona()\n    persona.breathe()\n\n\ndef reset_persona():\n    \"\"\"Reset for new session.\"\"\"\n    global _session_persona\n    _session_persona = Persona()\n    return _session_persona\n\n\ndef on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:\n\n[8 more lines in file. Use offset=440 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774238523407}}
{"type":"message","id":"90845001","parentId":"f1145555","timestamp":"2026-03-23T04:02:11.523Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me add the `run_spark()` function. I'll insert it before `on_spark()`. The function will:\n1. Run the SPARK drift chamber programmatically\n2. Return a spark_result dict in the expected format\n3. Call `on_spark()` internally to update personality\n\nBut actually, this is getting complex. SPARK needs an LLM to generate prose. The demo mode might not be fully working. And running the full SPARK drift + generation is non-trivial.\n\nLet me keep `run_spark()` simple: it runs the drift chamber and returns the concept activations + tensions, without the LLM generation step. The LLM generation is the slow/expensive part and might fail. I'll make it graceful.\n\n\nI'm going to build out the function to import the drift chamber and SPARK components, run the drift with appropriate parameters based on the mode, extract the top concepts and tensions, call `on_spark()` with that result, and return the voice guide.","thinkingSignature":"c3fdb669078ff85c8855686bca3fdff73b81566ce44c4b96c761174b9ab5a4b3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_5vesmcw6o3d1_1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\core\\persona.py","old_string":"def on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:","new_string":"def on_spark(spark_result: dict) -> str:"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":71774,"output":287,"cacheRead":13057,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":85118,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774238523416}}
